Overall, HPC sales growth moderated to \(+0.8\%\) (vs. \(+1.0\%\) last month) in the latest quad- week as volume growth slightly moderated on relatively flat pricing growth sequentially. Sales on promotions were down 40bps YoY. Growth was led by PG, which posted higher sales growth on higher pricing (alongside lower volume growth). CHD also posted modest sales growth, albeit at a decelerating rate, as volume declines accelerated to \(- 1.0\%\) (vs. \(+0.3\%\) prior). Sales trends were relatively flat for CL and KMB. CLX sales decelerated on sequentially lower volumes. KVUE also saw volume- led sales declines, as sales on promotions stepped down 530bps YoY.

Within non-alcoholic beverages, CSD \$ sales were up +5.0% for 2-wks (vs. +4.3% for 4-wks), Bottled Water \$ sales were up +2.9% for 2-wks (vs. +0.5% for 4-wks), Energy Drinks \$ sales were up +16.6% for 2-wks (vs. +16.4% for 4-wks), Sports Drinks \$ sales were up +3.5% for 2-wks (vs. +1.4% for 4-wks), RTD Coffee \$ sales were down -3.8% for 2-wks (vs. -3.7% for 4-wks), Coconut Water \$ sales were up +14.5% for 2-wks (vs. +13.7% for 4-wks), and Non-Alcoholic Beer \$ sales were up +24.7% for 2-wks (vs. +23.9% for 4-wks).

Within alcoholic beverages, Beer \$ sales were down -1.6% for 2-wks (vs. -2.1% for 4-wks), FMB/Cider/Seltzer \$ sales were down -2.6% for 2-wks (vs. -3.2% for 4-wks), Spirits \$ sales were up +2.3% for 2-wks (vs. +2.2% for 4-wks), and Wine \$ sales were down -2.7% for 2-wks (vs. -2.4% for 4-wks).

In tobacco/nicotine, Cigarette \$ sales were down -1.5% for 2-wks (vs. -2.1% for 4-wks), Chewing Tobacco \$ sales were up +14.4% for 2-wks (vs. +14.1% for 4-wks), and E-Cig \$ sales were down -18.2% for 2-wks (vs. -17.5% for 4-wks).

Retail \(\) sales for 4 wks ending 08/23 improved y/y across most companies (with mixed trends vs. prior month). By non-alcoholic beverage company, \(\) sales for MNST (ex-Bang) were up \(+9.2\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(+9.4\%\) last month), sales for KO were up \(+4.4\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(+5.7\%\) last month), sales for KDP were up \(+3.1\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(+3.4\%\) last month), sales for PEP were down \(-1.7\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-2.3\%\) last month), sales for ZVIA were up \(+19.7\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(+18.5\%\) last month), and sales for COCO were up \(+21.3\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(+20.7\%\) last month). By alcoholic beverage company, \(\) sales for SAM were down \(-3.8\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-5.3\%\) last month), sales for STZ were up \(+0.6\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-1.4\%\) last month), sales for TAP were down \(-4.8\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-6.4\%\) last month), and sales for BF were down \(-3.7\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-6.2\%\) last month). Within Tobacco, \(\) sales for BAT were up \(+0.2\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-1.0\%\) last month), sales for IMB were down \(-0.6\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-0.5\%\) last month), and sales for MO were down \(-2.7\%\) for 4- wks (vs. \(-3.2\%\) last month).

Packaged Food sales decelerated to \(- 1.3\%\) in the latest quad- week (vs \(- 1.0\%\) last month), driven by lower volumes and partially offset by higher prices. Within our coverage, sales decelerated for CAG and HSY primarily driven by lower volumes. On the other hand, sales improved for KHC and MDLZ due to higher prices, while the acceleration in sales for GIS, K, and SFD was driven by higher volumes. On a 12- week basis, sales decelerated across most of our coverage, noting KHC as the exception with a slight acceleration.
